      All Methods Instance Methods Concrete Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      Boolean high_granularity_filter()
      If true then will try to apply a high granularity to the filter requests, which will eliminate false positives but might also be expensive computationally If false then will never apply high granularity, there might be false positives if that is the more efficient (therefore a secondary test in sw might be required) If not specified then you should assume low granularity
      Boolean new_data_only()
      If true (defaults: false) then only new data is served to the job each time it runs (otherwise all data from the input matching the filter is served)
      Long size_batch_kb()
      When converting from streaming data to batch data, the max size of each batch in KBytes of record JSON string
      Long size_batch_records()
      When converting from streaming data to batch data, the max number of records in each batch
      Long test_record_limit_request()
      Sets a requested limit on the number of input records to be received - eg for test purposes The actual number might be different (eg multiplied by the number of distributed splits)
      String time_max()
      An optional human readable string that applies a time filter (upper bound) to the input data
      String time_min()
      An optional human readable string that applies a time filter (lower bound) to the input data
      Long timed_batch_ms()
      When converting from streaming data to batch data, the max time period over which to collect batches
